e-release-date-announced-e3-2019|title=Final Fantasy VII Remake Release Date Announced - E3 2019|first=Jonathan|last=Dornbush|date=June 9, 2019|publisher=[[Ziff Davis]]|work=[[IGN]]|accessdate=June 10, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190610042558/https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/06/10/final-fantasy-vii-remake-release-date-announced-e3-2019|archivedate=June 10, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"RemakeScale\">{{cite web|url=https://gematsu.com/2019/06/square-enix-uncertain-how-many-games-will-span-the-final-fantasy-vii-remake-project|title=Square Enix uncertain how many games will span the Final Fantasy VII Remake project [Update 2]|last=Romano|first=Sal|work=Gematsu|publisher=[[CraveOnline]]|date=June 11, 2019|accessdate=June 14, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190612053755/https://gematsu.com/2019/06/square-enix-uncertain-how-many-games-will-span-the-final-fantasy-vii-remake-project|archivedate=June 12, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"RemakeFirstInfo\">{{cite web|url=https://gematsu.com/2019/06/final-fantasy-vii-remake-e3-2019-trailer-stage-demo-special-editions-announced|title=Final Fantasy VII Remake E3 2019 trailer, stage demo; special editions announced|last=Romano|first=Sal|work=Gematsu|publisher=[[CraveOnline]]|date=June 11, 2019|accessdate=June 11, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190611211831/https://gematsu.com/2019/06/final-fantasy-vii-remake-e3-2019-trailer-stage-demo-special-editions-announced|archivedate=June 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|https://ffvii-remake.square-enix-games.com/}}\n* {{IMDb title|id=6057416}}\n\n{{FFVII|state=expand}}\n{{Final Fantasy series}}\n\n[[Category:2020 video games]]\n[[Category:Final Fantasy VII]]\n[[Category:Action role-playing video games]]\n[[Category:Climate change in fiction]]\n[[Category:Cyberpunk video games]]\n[[Category:Dystopian video games]]\n[[Category:Eco-terrorism in fiction]]\n[[Category:Environmental mass media]]\n[[Category:Final Fantasy video games]]\n[[Category:Japanese role-playing video games]]\n[[Category:Neo-noir video games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4 games]]\n[[Category:Science fiction video games]]\n[[Category:Single-player video games]]\n[[Category:Terrorism in fiction]]\n[[Category:Unreal Engine games]]\n[[Category:Video game remakes]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Japan]]\n[[Category:Video games directed by Tetsuya Nomura]]\n[[Category:Video games scored by Nobuo Uematsu]]\n", "name_user": "Alaios", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSales:fixed wording", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Final_Fantasy_VII_Remake"}
{"title_page": "Toy Retailers Association", "text_new": "{{Infobox company\n| name = The Toy Retailers Association\n| logo = \n| type = [[Trade association]]\n| genre = \n| foundation = {{start date and age|1950}}\n| location_city = [[Bodmin]], [[Cornwall]]\n| location_country = [[United Kingdom]]\n| key_people = Alan Simpson, [[Chairman]]\n| industry = [[Toy industry]]\n| homepage = [https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk toyretailersassociation.co.uk]\n}}\n\nThe '''Toy Retailers Association''' is a [[trade association]] that represents its members in the UK & Ireland. It promotes the role of the toy retailer and the value of toys to the consumer. It represents about 75% of the [[toy]] trade.<ref name=\"Guardian_2000-01-31\" /> It is based in [[Bodmin, Cornwall]].\n\n==History==\n\nThe Toy Retailers Association (TRA) was first established as the National Association of Toy Retailers in 1950 and changed its name first to the British Association of Toy Retailers (BATR) and then the Toy Retailers Association in 2005. It acts as both a watchdog and persuader to ensure fair play for toy retailers and represents the toy retail sector on government panels and safety organisations in the UK.\n\n==Awards==\nThe association organises DreamToys, where the top 12 and top 72 toys for Christmas are chosen every November. The press-only event is held at St Mary's Church in Marylebone, London.<ref name=\"dreamtoys\">{{cite web|url=https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk/dream-toys|title=DreamToys|last=|first=|date=November 13, 2019|work=toyretailersassociation.co.uk|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The TRA also organises the Toy of the Year Awards, an event where the Toy of the Year award and other prizes are presented, including Toy Shop of the Year, Supplier of the Year and Multiple Retailer of the Year. The event is held on the first night of the UK Toy Fair at Olympia, London, each year in January.\n\n==Affiliated members==\n* [[Early Learning Centre]]\n* [[Hamleys]]\n* [[The Entertainer (Amersham) Ltd.|The Entertainer]]\n* [[Smyths]]\n* [[Toytown Stores]]\n* [[Argos (retailer)|Argos]]\n* [[Toymaster]]\n\n==Toy of the Year==\n[[File:1964_Corgi_Aston_Martin_DB5.jpg|right|thumb|The first winner of Toy of the Year. The James Bond Aston Martin die-cast car]]\nThe Toy of the Year awards began in 1965 and are presented annually at an awarding dinner held during the [[British International Toy Fair]] at [[Olympia, London|Olympia]] in January. The criteria are that the toy must have been very popular in the past year and excited interest among customers and retailers in the toy market.\n* 1965 - [[James Bond]] [[Aston Martin]] [[die-cast toy|die-cast car]]<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1966 - [[Action Man]] ([[Palitoy]])<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1967 - [[Spirograph]] ([[Denys Fisher]])<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1968 - [[Sindy]] ([[Pedigree Dolls & Toys|Pedigree Toys]])<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1969 - [[Hot Wheels]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1970 - [[Sindy]]<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1971 - [[Katie Kopykat]] writing doll<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1972 - [[Plasticraft]] modelling kits<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1973 - [[Mastermind (board game)|Mastermind]] board game<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1974 - [[Lego]] Family set<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1975 - [[Lego]] Basic set<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1976 - [[Peter Powell (kite)]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1977 - [[Playmobil|Playmobil Playpeople]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1978 - [[Combine harvester|Combine Harvester]] ([[W. Britain|Britains Limited]])<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" /><ref name=\"V_and_A_Harvester\" />\n* 1979 - [[Lego Space|Legoland Space kits]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1980 - [[Rubik's Cube]]<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1981 - Rubik's Cube<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1982 - [[Kenner Star Wars action figures|Star Wars toys]]<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1983 - Star Wars toys<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1984 - [[Masters of the Universe]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1985 - [[Transformers (toy line)|Transformers]] ([[Optimus Prime]])<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1986 - [[Transformers (toy line)|Transformers]] ([[Optimus Prime]])<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1987 - [[Sylvanian Families]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1988 - Sylvanian Families<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1989 - Sylvanian Families<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1990 - [[Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles]]<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1991 - [[Game Boy|Nintendo Game Boy]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1992 - [[WWF Hasbro action figures|WWF Wrestlers]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1993 - [[Thunderbirds (TV series)|Thunderbirds]] [[Tracy Island]]<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1994 - [[Power Rangers]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1995 - [[Pogs]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1996 - [[Barbie]]<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1997 - [[Teletubbies]]<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1998 - [[Furby]]<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1999 - [[Furby|Furby Babies]]<ref name=\"Guardian_2000-01-31\" />\n* 2000 - [[Tekno the Robotic Puppy|Teksta]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 2001 - [[Bionicle]]s (Lego)<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 2002 - [[Beyblade]]s<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 2003 - [[Beyblade]]s<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 2004 - [[RoboSapien]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 2005 - [[Tamagotchi]] Connexion<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 2006 - [[Doctor Who]] [[Cyberman]] Mask<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 2007 - [[In the Night Garden...]] Blanket Time [[Iggle Piggle]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 2008 - [[Ben 10]] Action Figures 10\u201d and 15\u201d<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 2009 - [[Go Go Hamster]]s<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 2010 - Jet Pack [[Buzz Lightyear]]<ref name=\"toy2010\" />\n* 2011 - [[LeapPad Explorer]]<ref name=\"toy2011\" /><ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 2012 - [[Furby]]<ref name=\"toy2012\" />\n* 2013 - [[Tekno the Robotic Puppy|Teksta]]<ref name=\"toy2013\" />\n* 2014 - Disney [[Frozen (2013 film)|Frozen]] Snow Glow [[Elsa (Frozen)|Elsa]]<ref name=\"toy2014\" />\n* 2015 - Pie Face<ref name=\"toy2015\" />\n* 2016 - [[Hatchimals]]<ref name=\"toy2016\" />\n* 2017 - [[L.O.L. Surprise]]<ref name=\"toy2017\" />\n* 2018 - [[L.O.L. Surprise]]<ref name=\"toy2018\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"50years_bbc\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/av/business-37911284/over-50-years-of-toy-of-the-year|title=Over 50 years of toy of the year|website=BBC News|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"toy2010\">{{cite web|url=https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk/toy-year-2010|title=Toy of the Year 2010 - Toy Retailers Association|website=www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"toy2011\">{{cite web|url=https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk/toy-year-2011-0|title=Toy of the Year 2011 - Toy Retailers Association|website=www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"toy2012\">{{cite web|url=https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk/toy-year-2012|title=Toy of the Year 2012 - Toy Retailers Association|website=www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"toy2013\">{{cite web|url=https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk/toy-year-2013|title=Toy of the Year 2013 - Toy Retailers Association|website=www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"toy2014\">{{cite web|url=https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk/toy-year-2014|title=Toy of the Year 2014 - Toy Retailers Association|website=www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"toy2015\">{{cite web|url=https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk/toy-year-2015|title=Toy of the Year 2015 - Toy Retailers Association|website=www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"toy2016\">{{cite web|url=https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk/toy-year-2016|title=Toy of the Year 2016 - Toy Retailers Association|website=www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"toy2017\">{{cite web|url=https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk/toy-year-awards-2017|title=Toy of the Year Awards 2017 - Toy Retailers Association|website=www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"toy2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk/sites/default/files/press/releases/toyawards2018.pdf|title=Toy of the Year Awards 2018 - Toy Retailers Association|website=www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk|accessdate=10 August 2019}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Guardian_2000-01-31\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2000/jan/31/2|title=Lego is toy of the century|first=Guardian|last=staff|date=31 January 2000|website=the Guardian|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\">{{cite web|url=https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk/toy-year-1965-2007|title=Toy of the Year 1965-2007 - Toy Retailers Association|website=www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"V_and_A_Harvester\">{{cite web|url=https://collections.vam.ac.uk/item/O176713/mf-massey-ferguson-760-combine-harvester-britains-ltd/|title=MF Massey Ferguson, 760 - Britains Ltd - V&A Search the Collections|website=collections.vam.ac.uk|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.batr.co.uk Toy Retailers Association]\n* [http://www.btha.co.uk British Toy and Hobby Association]\n\n[[Category:Trade associations based in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Toy companies of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in Lincolnshire]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 1950]]\n[[Category:Toy retailers]]\n[[Category:1950 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Toy industry]]\n[[Category:Children's media and toys awards]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company\n| name = The Toy Retailers Association\n| logo = \n| type = [[Trade association]]\n| genre = \n| foundation = {{start date and age|1950}}\n| location_city = [[Bodmin]], [[Cornwall]]\n| location_country = [[United Kingdom]]\n| key_people = Alan Simpson, [[Chairman]]\n| industry = [[Toy industry]]\n| homepage = [https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk toyretailersassociation.co.uk]\n}}\n\nThe '''Toy Retailers Association''' is a [[trade association]] that represents its members in the UK & Ireland. It promotes the role of the toy retailer and the value of toys to the consumer. It represents about 75% of the [[toy]] trade.<ref name=\"Guardian_2000-01-31\" /> It is based in [[Bodmin, Cornwall]].\n\n==History==\n\nThe Toy Retailers Association (TRA) was first established as the National Association of Toy Retailers in 1950 and changed its name first to the British Association of Toy Retailers (BATR) and then the Toy Retailers Association in 2005. It acts as both a watchdog and persuader to ensure fair play for toy retailers and represents the toy retail sector on government panels and safety organisations in the UK.\n\n==Awards==\nThe association organises DreamToys, where the top 12 and top 72 toys for Christmas are chosen every November. The press-only event is held at St Mary's Church in Marylebone, London. <ref name=\"dreamtoys\">{{cite web|url=https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk/dream-toys|title=DreamToys|last=|first=|date=November 13, 2019|work=toyretailersassociation.co.uk|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The TRA also organises the Toy of the Year Awards, an event where the Toy of the Year award and other prizes are presented, including Toy Shop of the Year, Supplier of the Year and Multiple Retailer of the Year. The event is held on the first night of the UK Toy Fair at Olympia, London, each year in January.\n\n==Affiliated members==\n* [[Early Learning Centre]]\n* [[Hamleys]]\n* [[The Entertainer (Amersham) Ltd.|The Entertainer]]\n* [[Smyths]]\n* [[Toytown Stores]]\n* [[Argos]]\n* [[Toymaster]]\n\n==Toy of the Year==\n[[File:1964_Corgi_Aston_Martin_DB5.jpg|right|thumb|The first winner of Toy of the Year. The James Bond Aston Martin die-cast car]]\nThe Toy of the Year awards began in 1965 and are presented annually at an awarding dinner held during the [[British International Toy Fair]] at [[Olympia, London|Olympia]] in January. The criteria are that the toy must have been very popular in the past year and excited interest among customers and retailers in the toy market.\n* 1965 - [[James Bond]] [[Aston Martin]] [[die-cast toy|die-cast car]]<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1966 - [[Action Man]] ([[Palitoy]])<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1967 - [[Spirograph]] ([[Denys Fisher]])<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1968 - [[Sindy]] ([[Pedigree Dolls & Toys|Pedigree Toys]])<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1969 - [[Hot Wheels]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1970 - [[Sindy]]<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1971 - [[Katie Kopykat]] writing doll<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1972 - [[Plasticraft]] modelling kits<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1973 - [[Mastermind (board game)|Mastermind]] board game<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1974 - [[Lego]] Family set<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1975 - [[Lego]] Basic set<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1976 - [[Peter Powell (kite)]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1977 - [[Playmobil|Playmobil Playpeople]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1978 - [[Combine harvester|Combine Harvester]] ([[W. Britain|Britains Limited]])<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" /><ref name=\"V_and_A_Harvester\" />\n* 1979 - [[Lego Space|Legoland Space kits]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1980 - [[Rubik's Cube]]<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1981 - Rubik's Cube<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1982 - [[Kenner Star Wars action figures|Star Wars toys]]<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1983 - Star Wars toys<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1984 - [[Masters of the Universe]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1985 - [[Transformers (toy line)|Transformers]] ([[Optimus Prime]])<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1986 - [[Transformers (toy line)|Transformers]] ([[Optimus Prime]])<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1987 - [[Sylvanian Families]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1988 - Sylvanian Families<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1989 - Sylvanian Families<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1990 - [[Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles]]<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1991 - [[Game Boy|Nintendo Game Boy]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1992 - [[WWF Hasbro action figures|WWF Wrestlers]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1993 - [[Thunderbirds (TV series)|Thunderbirds]] [[Tracy Island]]<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1994 - [[Power Rangers]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1995 - [[Pogs]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 1996 - [[Barbie]]<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1997 - [[Teletubbies]]<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1998 - [[Furby]]<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 1999 - [[Furby|Furby Babies]]<ref name=\"Guardian_2000-01-31\" />\n* 2000 - [[Tekno the Robotic Puppy|Teksta]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 2001 - [[Bionicle]]s (Lego)<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 2002 - [[Beyblade]]s<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 2003 - [[Beyblade]]s<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 2004 - [[RoboSapien]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 2005 - [[Tamagotchi]] Connexion<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 2006 - [[Doctor Who]] [[Cyberman]] Mask<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 2007 - [[In the Night Garden...]] Blanket Time [[Iggle Piggle]]<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 2008 - [[Ben 10]] Action Figures 10\u201d and 15\u201d<ref name=\"Toy_1965-2007\" />\n* 2009 - [[Go Go Hamster]]s<ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 2010 - Jet Pack [[Buzz Lightyear]]<ref name=\"toy2010\" />\n* 2011 - [[LeapPad Explorer]]<ref name=\"toy2011\" /><ref name=\"50years_bbc\" />\n* 2012 - [[Furby]]<ref name=\"toy2012\" />\n* 2013 - [[Tekno the Robotic Puppy|Teksta]]<ref name=\"toy2013\" />\n* 2014 - Disney [[Frozen (2013 film)|Frozen]] Snow Glow [[Elsa (Frozen)|Elsa]]<ref name=\"toy2014\" />\n* 2015 - Pie Face<ref name=\"toy2015\" />\n* 2016 - [[Hatchimals]]<ref name=\"toy2016\" />\n* 2017 - [[L.O.L. Surprise]]<ref name=\"toy2017\" />\n* 2018 - [[L.O.L. Surprise]]<ref name=\"toy2018\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"50years_bbc\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/av/business-37911284/over-50-years-of-toy-of-the-year|title=Over 50 years of toy of the year|website=BBC News|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"toy2010\">{{cite web|url=https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk/toy-year-2010|title=Toy of the Year 2010 - Toy Retailers Association|website=www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"toy2011\">{{cite web|url=https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk/toy-year-2011-0|title=Toy of the Year 2011 - Toy Retailers Association|website=www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"toy2012\">{{cite web|url=https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk/toy-year-2012|title=Toy of the Year 2012 - Toy Retailers Association|website=www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"toy2013\">{{cite web|url=https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk/toy-year-2013|title=Toy of the Year 2013 - Toy Retailers Association|website=www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"toy2014\">{{cite web|url=https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk/toy-year-2014|title=Toy of the Year 2014 - Toy Retailers Association|website=www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"toy2015\">{{cite web|url=https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk/toy-year-2015|title=Toy of the Year 2015 - Toy Retailers Association|website=www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"toy2016\">{{cite web|url=https://www.toyretailersassociation.co.uk/toy-year-2016|title=Toy of the Year 2016 - Toy Retailers Associatio