rms First Case of Coronavirus|date=2020-02-26|website=Civil.ge|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227050210/https://civil.ge/archives/340246|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://agenda.ge/en/news/2020/620|title=Georgia reports second case of coronavirus|website=Agenda.ge|access-date=2020-02-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228181135/https://agenda.ge/en/news/2020/620|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*On 28 February, [[Belarus]] confirmed its first case. A student from [[Iran]] tested positive on 27 February and was admitted to a hospital in [[Minsk]].<ref name=\"minzdrav\">{{Cite web|url=http://minzdrav.gov.by/sobytiya/v-belarusi-zaregistrirovan-zavoznoy-sluchay-koronavirusa/|title=\u0423 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0456 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u044d\u0433\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043d\u044b \u0437\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0437\u043d\u044b \u0432\u044b\u043f\u0430\u0434\u0430\u043a \u043a\u0430\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0456\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430|last=|first=|date=|website=minzdrav.gov.by|language=ru|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-belarus-idUSKCN20M0IH|title=Belarus announces first case of coronavirus: TASS|date=2020-02-28|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-03-04|language=en}}</ref> The individual arrived in Belarus via a flight from [[Baku]], [[Azerbaijan]], on 22 February.<ref name=minzdrav /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/belarus-reports-first-confirmed-coronavirus-case/30459212.html|title=Four Lawmakers In Iran Test Positive As Coronavirus Forces Cancellation Of Friday Prayers|website=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty|language=en|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref>\n*On 11 March, Health Ministry of Kuwait confirmed two people to have [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]], who came in contact with an infected person whom arrived in [[Kuwait]] from Azerbaijan.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/asia-pacific/coronavirus-cases-in-kuwait-up-to-72/1762188|title=Coronavirus cases in Kuwait up to 72|website=www.aa.com.tr|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref>\n\n==Evacuation of citizens ==\n\n* On 1 February, [[Turkey|Turkey's]] [[Ministry of Health (Turkey)|health minister]] [[Fahrettin Koca]]''',''' has said a total of 44 people, including 34 Turkish citizens, 6 Azerbaijanis, 3 Georgians and 1 Albanian have been evacuated from Wuhan.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/cloneofcloneofcloneofcloneofchina-battles-corona-200130230453300.html|title=Coronavirus spreads to more countries: All the latest updates|publisher=Al Jazeera|access-date=24 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200220065432/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/cloneofcloneofcloneofcloneofchina-battles-corona-200130230453300.html|archive-date=20 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/asia-pacific/turkey-begins-evacuation-of-turks-from-china-/1720864|title=Turkey begins evacuation of Turks from China|website=www.aa.com.tr|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref>\n* On 15 March, charter flights started to launch for the return of Azerbaijan citizens from Turkey since mutual trips of Turkish and Azerbaijani citizens by air and land have been temporarily suspended to prevent the spread of coronavirus. Those returned from Turkey quarantined for 14\u201328 days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.trend.az/azerbaijan/society/3207731.html|title=Azerbaijani citizens to return from Turkey on charter flights|date=2020-03-15|website=Trend.Az|language=en|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n* On 17 March, Azerbaijan started to launch charter flights from [[European Union]] countries, Russia and other countries to evacuate citizens.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.trend.az/azerbaijan/society/3210767.html|title=Azerbaijan brings back over 1,700 of its citizens amid coronavirus epidemic|date=2020-03-19|website=Trend.Az|language=en|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n\n==Impact==\n\n* On 4 March, first tour of the Baku Road Bicycle Racing Cup (supposed to be held on March 7\u20138) and Azerbaijani Basketball Championship matches have been cancelled.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.trend.az/azerbaijan/society/3201178.html|title=Azerbaijan cancels sporting events|website=www.en.trend.az/|date=4 March 2020|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref> On 10 March, the traditional festivities related to [[Novruz in Azerbaijan|Novruz holiday in Baku and Azerbaijan's regions]] in March have been canceled.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.trend.az/azerbaijan/society/3204719.html|title=Azerbaijan cancels traditional festivities related to Novruz holiday|website=www.en.trend.az/|date=10 March 2020|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref>\n* On 13 March, 55th European Karate Championship (supposed to be held on March 25\u201329) had been cancelled.<ref>{{cite web |title=EKF Senior Championships cancelled over coronavirus outbreak |url=https://www.wkf.net/news-center-new/ekf-senior-championships-cancelled-over-coronavirus-outbreak/1252 |website=www.wkf.net |accessdate=14 March 2020 |language=en |date=13 March 2020}}</ref> Also the [[2019\u201320 Azerbaijan Premier League|Azerbaijan Premier League]] was postponed due to the pandemic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://azertag.az/en/xeber/Premier_League_suspended_as_coronavirus_continues_to_trouble_football-1440427|title=Premier League suspended as coronavirus continues to trouble football|last=|first=|date=|website=AZERTAC|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>  Additionally the finals for the [[2020 FIG Artistic Gymnastics World Cup series|Baku World Cup]] for artistic gymnastics (scheduled for 14\u201315 March) was cancelled after qualifications had already taken place.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gymnastics.sport/site/news/displaynews.php?idNews=2836|title=Finals of Baku World Cup cancelled|work=[[International Gymnastics Federation]]|date=March 13, 2020}}</ref>\n* On 17 March, UEFA announced that [[UEFA Euro 2020]] (Azerbaijan is one of the host countries) would be delayed by a year due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe]].<ref name=\"postponed\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51909518|title=Euro 2020 postponed until next summer, says the Norwegian FA|website=bbc.co.uk|publisher=[[BBC News]]|date=17 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n* On 23 March,  organisers of the [[Azerbaijan Grand Prix]] announced that [[2020 Formula One World Championship|the race]] had been postponed.<ref name=\"Baku postponed\">{{cite web|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.azerbaijan-grand-prix-postponed-as-coronavirus-outbreak-continues.1RWvgRPIc71u9JtHft14eE.html|title=Azerbaijan Grand Prix postponed as coronavirus outbreak continues|website=formula1.com|date=23 March 2020|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Azerbaijan|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Azerbaijan]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Azerbaijan]]\n[[Category:2020 in Azerbaijan|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Azerbaijan]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Asia|Azerbaijan]]\n", "text_old": "{{current||pandemic}}\n{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Azerbaijan}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Azerbaijan\n| map1            = COVID-19 pandemic Cases in Azerbaijan.svg\n| legend1         = Number of confirmed cases by regions<br>(as of 5 April): {{legend|#FFD5D5|Confirmed 1}}\n{{legend|#FF8080|Confirmed 2~5}}\n{{legend|#FF2A2A|Confirmed 6~10}}\n{{legend|#D40000|Confirmed 11~100}}\n{{legend|#800000|Confirmed \u2265100}}\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3   